---
name: Estate Auctions
history:
- Created by Proposal 7846 (o, Aris), 8 May 2017
- Amended(1) by Proposal 7864 (Aris, G., o, nichdel, Publius Scribonius Scholasticus), 27 June 2017
- Amended(2) by Proposal 7868 "Minor economic fixes" (Murphy), 30 July 2017
text: |
  At the start of each month, if Agora owns at least one Estate,
  the Surveyor shall put one Estate which is owned by Agora up for
  auction, by announcement. Each auction ends seven days after it
  begins.
  
  During an auction, any player or organization may bid any number of
  Shinies by announcement. AWithin a week after the end of an auction, if there
  is a single highest bid on that auction, the player or Organization that
  placed that bid can cause Agora to transfer the auctioned Estate to emself by
  paying Agora the number of Shinies stated in that bid. If the highest bidder
  does not do so in a timely fashion, the Surveyor shall issue the player who
  submitted the bid a Yellow Card.
id: 2491
rev: 2
power: 2
